posts.title: Batman
posts.description: Batman is a fictional superhero created by Bob Kane and Bill Finger, first appearing in Detective Comics #27. He is known for his detective skills, martial arts expertise, and use of advanced technology in his fight against crime in Gotham City.

posts.title: CSS
posts.description: CSS, or Cascading Style Sheets, is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in a markup language, such as HTML. It controls how HTML elements are displayed on a webpage, including aspects like fonts, colors, spacing, and layout. CSS is a core technology of the World Wide Web, alongside HTML and JavaScript.
